                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17811205-50-off266 t17811205-50-crimeloc267"></join>, he found a number of people about his door, who informed him, a woman, who was the prisoner at the bar, had stole a copper turbot-pan and cover from the door; the prisoner was then in custody in his shop. (The pan was produced in court, and deposed to by him as his property.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17811205-50-person569">
                  John
                   Punnel
               <interp inst="t17811205-50-person569" type="surname" value="Punnel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17811205-50-person569" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17811205-50-person569" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             deposed, he was in the shop about five o'clock, and saw the woman put something under her cloak; laid hold of her, and took it from her; that she had got about three yards from the shop, when he stopt her. His master is a broker; I brought her back to the shop.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was coming down this place, called <placeName id="t17811205-50-crimeloc268">Broker's Alley</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17811205-50-crimeloc268" type="placeName" value="Broker's Alley"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17811205-50-crimeloc268" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17811205-50-off266 t17811205-50-crimeloc268"></join>; my gown pulled it down, and I picked it up, and this man came by and laid hold on me, and carried me into the shop; the woman asked me how I came by it, and whether I was going to steal it: I told her No.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17811205-50-verdict269" type="verdictDescription">
